methods.getGroupingForKeySet:
Return a grouping that contains row keys that match the values in keys.

:param keys: (java.util.Set<java.lang.Object>) - A set of values that TupleSource should match. For a single ColumnSource, the values
        within the set are the values that we would like to find. For compound TupleSource instances, the
        values are SmartKeys.
:param tupleSource: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.tuples.TupleSource) - The tuple factory for singular or compound keys
:return: (java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.utils.RowSet>) A map from keys to RowSet, for each of the keys present in this row set's
         view of tupleSource
methods.getSubSetForKeySet:
Return a subset that contains row keys that match the values in keys.

:param keys: (java.util.Set<java.lang.Object>) - A set of values that TupleSource should match. For a single ColumnSource, the values
        within the set are the values that we would like to find. For compound TupleSource instances, the
        values are SmartKeys.
:param tupleSource: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.tuples.TupleSource) - The tuple factory for singular or compound keys
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.utils.RowSet) A MutableRowSet with all row keys from this RowSet whose value in tupleSource was present
         in keys
